title: For Sale:  VEPR Hunter 7.62X54R (WTT for guitar equipment)
postcontent:
After much rumination, I have decided to put my Russian built Molot VEPR Hunter in 7.62X54R up for sale. If you are unfamiliar with this rifle or manufacturer, I suggest doing a little reading up on them. They are known as one of the highest quality AK/Kalashnikov makers on the market today. With their heavy duty RPK style receivers, and top level manufacturing specs, you can't do much better than a VEPR. This rifle is unique in that, while being based on Kalashnikov's time tested design, it has many features of a regular hunting rifle. It has a push button safety (also the bolt hold open button), and a full length Russian walnut stock, rather than the standard two piece AK design. The beauty of the stock itself must be seen in person. It has a built in muzzle brake on the fluted barrel, and the trigger group in this rifle is far superior to that of a standard AK. It also comes with a serial number matched side rail scope mount. I am including a Nikon Prostaff scope with Butler Creek flip up covers and rings which has just been boresighted. The scope is under 1 year old (with original receipt) and the rifle is under 2 years old. I took it to the range a few times and it has been in the safe since. The gun is amazingly accurate. I have another VEPR in 7.62 so I am having trouble reconciling the idea of why I need two. The rifle has less than 200 rounds through it and is in PERFECT shape. It is like a brand new rifle. It comes with the original manual and cleaning kit, and two 5 round mags. Centerfire systems usually has these for around 13 hundred bucks (excluding taxes and background fees), but they appear to be out of them now. I am incuding a link to the Molot website so you can see how much they are asking when they are in stock, which they aren't at the moment. I will include the scope, mount, rings, sling, 150 rounds of Bulgarian surplus ammo, and a nice case for the asking price of $1200 FIRM. Please respect my asking price and do not contact me with lowball offers. I am not in financial straits and do not need to sell it. I will ONLY sell it for the right price. The only trades I would consider would be for a QUALITY American made guitar like a Gibson Les Paul or a vintage American Strat. I would also trade for a quality tube amp and/or 4X12 cabinets like those made by Orange, Marshall, or Mesa Boogie. If I am uninterested I will not respond. Please do not take offense. Cash is most likely going to be king on this transaction. You may call or text 8 five 0 - six three 7 - two 9 eight 5 with any questions or concerns or reply via REDACTED. title: For Sale:  NIB Benelli M4 Tactical 12ga
postcontent: Factory New Benelli M4 Tactical 12 gauge shotgun. Benelli has long been renowned for their world class sporting shotguns. Their attention to detail, craftsmanship and innovative recoil system make them some of the most desired guns on the market. In the early 90s Benelli released a "Tactical" version of their popular M1 Super 90 shotgun. While this gun was exceedingly light and functioned flawlessly in it's stock configuration it did have some short comings. During military evaluation of the M1 Super 90 it was determined that Benelli's standard Inertia system has cycling issues when large amount of weight (such as a night vision optic) was added to the system. Benelli's answer to this problem is the M4 Tactical. This shotgun utilizes their revolutionary A.R.G.O. short stroke gas piston system. This operating system employs 2 short stroke gas pistons as opposed to the 1 long stroke gas piston found in a typical Browning design. This change provides reduced bolt wear, greatly increased reliability and longer time between cleanings. This operating system is also self regulating and self cleaning, virtually eliminating gas system maintenance. The M4 Tactical features ghost ring style sights and a factory installed picatinny optics rail.
